deficits (Roca et al., 2010) and that functional deficits are 
unrelated to lesion location within the frontal lobe 
(Salthouse, 2005). After an extensive review, Barceló & 
Santomé-Calleja (2000) concluded that studies strongly 
suggest that the concept of anatomically “pure” tasks of 
EF is deceptive.
Increasing data from connectionist models (Chaytor 
& Schmitter-Edgecombe, 2007) and from connectionist 
vertical brain models (Koziol & Budding, 2009) suggest 
that cognitive functioning is best represented by inte-
grated small-world networks and that specific brain 
regions are recruited by a number of cognitive systems 
and activities. For example, Simões-Franklin, Hester, 
Shpaner, Foxe, & Garavan (2010) found that the dorsal 
